ide to [OpenCode](https://opencode.ai) — from your first prompt to custom agents, skills, plugins, and MCP integrations. Built around clear mental models and real examples, not marketing.\n\n[![License: MIT](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/942e017bf0672002dd32a857c95d66f28c5900ab541838c6c664442516309c8a/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f6c6963656e73652d4d49542d626c75652e7376673f7374796c653d666c61742d737175617265)](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/LICENSE)\n[![OpenCode v1.16.2](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/d91964d493f6e09e94a4214c43389d7a99c2bc2f3fce33211fe05378673529d8/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f4f70656e436f64652d76312e31362e322d3743334145443f7374796c653d666c61742d737175617265)](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/releases)\n[![Last reviewed](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/6bb386d4dbca7a41bc0e338679fb5f71e579c74ff322304f716602820197a569/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f6c61737425323072657669657765642d4a756e65253230323032362d3232633535653f7374796c653d666c61742d737175617265)](#updates--deprecations)\n[![PRs welcome](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/b48efa9867bbd52c3af5f6a0793b8a344c49fd9fd22868c47fc5383617f8b454/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f5052732d77656c636f6d652d6666363962343f7374796c653d666c61742d737175617265)](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md)\n\n![License: MIT](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/942e017bf0672002dd32a857c95d66f28c5900ab541838c6c664442516309c8a/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f6c6963656e73652d4d49542d626c75652e7376673f7374796c653d666c61742d737175617265)\n![OpenCode v1.16.2](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/d91964d493f6e09e94a4214c43389d7a99c2bc2f3fce33211fe05378673529d8/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f4f70656e436f64652d76312e31362e322d3743334145443f7374796c653d666c61742d737175617265)\n![Last reviewed](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/6bb386d4dbca7a41bc0e338679fb5f71e579c74ff322304f716602820197a569/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f6c61737425323072657669657765642d4a756e65253230323032362d3232633535653f7374796c653d666c61742d737175617265)\n![PRs welcome](https://camo.githubusercontent.com/b48efa9867bbd52c3af5f6a0793b8a344c49fd9fd22868c47fc5383617f8b454/68747470733a2f2f696d672e736869656c64732e696f2f62616467652f5052732d77656c636f6d652d6666363962343f7374796c653d666c61742d737175617265)\n\n**Who this is for:** Developers using (or about to use) [OpenCode](https://opencode.ai). Beginners get a guided path; power users get depth on Custom Commands, Skills, Plugins, MCP, and Agents.\n\n⚖️ **Not affiliated with the OpenCode team.** This is a community-maintained guide. For canonical sources, check [opencode.ai/docs](https://opencode.ai/docs/) and [github.com/anomalyco/opencode](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode).\n\n## 🧭 Choose your path\n\n| You are… | Start with | Time |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| 🚀 **New to OpenCode** | [What is it](#what-is-opencode) → [Setup](#setup) → [Prompt Engineering](#prompt-engineering) | ~15 min |\n| ⚡ **Already using it** | [Custom Commands](#custom-commands) · [Skills](#agent-skills) · [Plugins](#plugins) · [MCP](#mcp-servers) | ~20 min each |\n| 🧠 **Configuring or headless** | [Agents](#agents) · [Headless & CI](#headless--ci) · [Models & Providers](#models--providers) | varies |\n\n## Getting started\n\n### What is OpenCode?\n\nOpenCode is an open-source AI coding agent — a terminal app (TUI), desktop app, and IDE extension that reads your repo, runs commands, edits files, and talks to any LLM you point it at. Maintained by [Anomaly](https://github.com/anomalyco), MIT-licensed.\n\n**Three things it does that a chat UI can't:**\n\n`read`\n`grep`\n`glob`\n`edit`\n`write`\n`apply_patch`\n`bash`\n\n**Three interfaces:**\n\n| Surface | Command | When |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **TUI** (default) | `opencode` | Interactive day-to-day work in your terminal |\n| **CLI / headless** | `opencode run \"<prompt>\"` | Scripts, CI jobs, one-shot prompts |\n| **Server** | `opencode serve` or `opencode web` | Headless API, web UI, or remote attach |\n\n`opencode`\n`opencode run \"<prompt>\"`\n`opencode serve`\n`opencode web`\n\nOpenCode sits in the same space as Claude Code, Cursor, and Aider — same problem, different trade-offs. None is universally better; pick the one whose model, surface, and ecosystem fit your workflow.\n\n⚠️ **AI-coding caveat:** OpenCode (like every coding agent) can produce wrong code, miss edge cases, hallucinate APIs, and over-apply patterns. **You're still the reviewer.** Read diffs before accepting, run tests, and don't auto-approve destructive operations on code you care about.\n\n### When OpenCode isn't the right tool\n\n| Limitation | Detail |\n| --- | --- |\n| **No inline editor completion** | OpenCode is a conversational agent, not Copilot-style autocomplete. For ghost-text-while-you-type, reach for [Copilot](https://github.com/features/copilot), [Cursor Tab](https://cursor.sh/), [Codeium](https://codeium.com/), or [Supermaven](https://supermaven.com/) — or alongside. |\n| **Quality depends on the underlying model** | OpenCode doesn't replace the LLM's reasoning. If your task fails on Sonnet, switching to OpenCode won't fix it. |\n| **Provider-agnostic ≠ provider-equivalent** | Some models tool-call better than others. A slug swap isn't free. |\n| **TUI on slow SSH / minimal terminals** | The TUI uses truecolor and complex layouts. Degrades over slow connections. `opencode serve` + `attach` or `opencode run` are better for those cases. |\n| **Plugins run arbitrary code** | Any plugin — local or npm — has full user permissions. Audit before installing. |\n| **Free Zen models are time-limited** | The [Zen docs](https://opencode.ai/docs/zen) call them \"available for a limited time.\" Don't build production on them. |\n| **Docs lag shipping** | OpenCode moves fast. This guide and even the official docs occasionally trail the actual binary. |\n| **Not a substitute for code review** | Diff-aware edits + passing tests don't guarantee correct, secure, or maintainable code. Treat AI output as a junior teammate's PR. |\n\n`opencode serve`\n`attach`\n`opencode run`\n\n**When something else fits better:**\n\nOpenCode's trade-off: flexibility and openness over polish and single-vendor integration. Worth it for many use cases; not all.\n\n### Setup\n\n⏱️ **5 minutes** from zero to first AI-assisted commit.\n\n#### 1. Install\n\nOther supported installers (pick whichever you already use):\n\nA desktop app for macOS / Windows / Linux is in beta at [opencode.ai/download](https://opencode.ai/download).\n\n#### 2. Authenticate\n\nOr from inside the TUI: `/connect`. Provider options covered in the next section.\n\n`/connect`\n\n#### 3. First prompt\n\nTry one of these:\n\n`explain what this codebase does`\n`add a README section about installation`\n`find and fix the failing test in src/api.test.ts`\n\n#### 4. Generate an `AGENTS.md`\n\n`AGENTS.md`\n`/init`\n\n`/init` generates an `AGENTS.md` — your project's \"house rules\" that OpenCode reads every session. Commit it. More in [Prompt Engineering](#prompt-engineering).\n\n`/init`\n`AGENTS.md`\n\n📝 **Coming from Claude Code?** OpenCode reads `CLAUDE.md` as a fallback if no `AGENTS.md` exists. Disable with `OPENCODE_DISABLE_CLAUDE_CODE=1` once migrated.\n\n`CLAUDE.md`\n`AGENTS.md`\n`OPENCODE_DISABLE_CLAUDE_CODE=1`\n\n#### 5. (Bonus) See a real configured project\n\nThis repo's own [`.opencode/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode) directory is a working example:\n\n`.opencode/`\n\n| Path | What it does |\n| --- | --- |\n| [`.opencode/agents/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/agents) | Custom agent definitions (markdown + YAML) |\n| [`.opencode/commands/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/commands) | Custom slash commands |\n| [`.opencode/plugins/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/plugins) | Working JS plugins (audit log, secret blocker) |\n| [`.opencode/skills/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/skills) | Agent skills with `SKILL.md` files |\n| [`AGENTS.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/AGENTS.md) | Project instructions OpenCode reads every session |\n| [`opencode.json`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/opencode.json) | Project config with safe defaults |\n\n`.opencode/agents/`\n`.opencode/commands/`\n`.opencode/plugins/`\n`.opencode/skills/`\n`SKILL.md`\n`AGENTS.md`\n`opencode.json`\n\n### Models & Providers\n\nOpenCode is **provider-agnostic**. Three ways to plug in a model — pick whichever fits your accounts, budget, and privacy posture:\n\n|  | Best for | Trade-off |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Direct providers** (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, Groq, OpenRouter, AWS Bedrock, Azure) | You already have credits with a provider | Manage one key per provider |\n| **[OpenCode Zen](#opencode-zen)** — pay-as-you-go gateway | One key, curated lineup, no commitment | Pricier per token than going direct in some cases |\n| **Local models** (Ollama, LM Studio, llama.cpp) | Offline, strict data-residency, hobbyist | Quality varies hugely with model and hardware |\n\nThere's no universally right answer — pick what fits.\n\n#### Direct provider config\n\nVariable substitution: `{env:NAME}` (environment) or `{file:./path}` (file content, absolute or relative).\n\n`{env:NAME}`\n`{file:./path}`\n\nPer-agent model override:\n\n#### OpenCode Zen\n\nA curated, pay-as-you-go AI gateway. The OpenCode team tests and tunes models for coding-agent workloads; you get one key and a benchmarked lineup. Reference Zen models with the `opencode/<model-id>` namespace.\n\n`opencode/<model-id>`\n\n**Pricing snapshot** *(verified 2026-06-08; check [opencode.ai/docs/zen](https://opencode.ai/docs/zen) for current)*\n\n| Model ID | Input / Output (per MTok) | Reach for it when… |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `opencode/claude-opus-4-8` | $5 / $25 | Flagship reasoning — complex refactors, large multi-file work |\n| `opencode/claude-sonnet-4-6` | $3 / $15 | Balanced everyday coding |\n| `opencode/claude-haiku-4-5` | $1 / $5 | Fast, lightweight tasks |\n| `opencode/gpt-5.5` *(≤272K)* | $5 / $30 | Long-context, OpenAI ecosystem |\n| `opencode/gpt-5.4-mini` | $0.75 / $4.50 | Cost-efficient frontier |\n| `opencode/gemini-3.1-pro` | $2 / $12 | Multimodal, Google ecosystem |\n| `opencode/qwen3.7-plus` | $0.40 / $1.60 | Budget-friendly heavy lifting |\n\n`opencode/claude-opus-4-8`\n`opencode/claude-sonnet-4-6`\n`opencode/claude-haiku-4-5`\n`opencode/gpt-5.5`\n`opencode/gpt-5.4-mini`\n`opencode/gemini-3.1-pro`\n`opencode/qwen3.7-plus`\n\n**Free tier** *(rotating, time-limited, for community feedback):* `big-pickle` *(stealth)*, `deepseek-v4-flash-free`, `mimo-v2.5-free`, `nemotron-3-ultra-free`.\n\n`big-pickle`\n`deepseek-v4-flash-free`\n`mimo-v2.5-free`\n`nemotron-3-ultra-free`\n\n50+ models total — full list, cached-read/write rates, GPT-5 Codex variants, Gemini, GLM, Kimi, MiniMax, Grok, and the Claude Opus 4.8/4.7/4.5/4.1 line: [opencode.ai/docs/zen](https://opencode.ai/docs/zen) · Deeper guide: [`docs/zen.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/zen.md).\n\n`docs/zen.md`\n\n💡 **Pattern: cheap explorer / strong executor.** Use a cheap model (`qwen3.7-plus`, `gpt-5.4-mini`) for `explore` and `scout` subagents that read a lot, and a stronger one (`claude-sonnet-4-6` or `claude-opus-4-8`) for the main `build` agent that does the editing.\n\n`qwen3.7-plus`\n`gpt-5.4-mini`\n`explore`\n`scout`\n`claude-sonnet-4-6`\n`claude-opus-4-8`\n`build`\n\n## Using OpenCode\n\n### Prompt Engineering\n\n**📖 Project Initialization.** Run `/init` to auto-generate an `AGENTS.md`. Treat it like any frequently-used prompt — iterate on it. Don't just dump 500 lines and forget.\n\n`/init`\n`AGENTS.md`\n\n#### Plan → Build cycle\n\nTwo primary agents you toggle with **Tab**:\n\n| Agent | What changes | Use it for |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **`plan`** | `edit` and `bash` default to `ask` — analysis without surprise writes | Reading code, designing approaches, reviewing diffs |\n| **`build`** | Full tool access (default) | Implementation, refactors, running tests |\n\n`plan`\n`edit`\n`bash`\n`ask`\n`build`\n\nNatural workflow:\n\n`[plan] > how would you implement OAuth for this app?\n(reads, plans, proposes — no writes)\n[plan] > <Tab>\n[build] > do it\n(implements, edits, runs tests)`\n\n💡 Prompts like `think hard`, `think more`, or `ultrathink` nudge reasoning depth on supported models — the same pattern in the [Anthropic prompt engineering guide](https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/build-with-claude/prompt-engineering/overview).\n\n`think hard`\n`think more`\n`ultrathink`\n\n#### File references and shell\n\n| Syntax | Effect | Example |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `@<path>` | Attach file content (fuzzy resolved) | `look at @src/api/auth.ts` |\n| `!<cmd>` | Run shell, inject output | `!git diff` then ask about it |\n\n`@<path>`\n`look at @src/api/auth.ts`\n`!<cmd>`\n`!git diff`\n`> review @packages/api/src/handlers/auth.ts for missing input validation\n> !pnpm test --reporter=verbose\n> based on those failures, fix the auth handler`\n\n#### `AGENTS.md` for project rules\n\n`AGENTS.md`\n\nReads on every session. Add extra files via `instructions: [\"...\"]` in `opencode.json`.\n\n`instructions: [\"...\"]`\n`opencode.json`\n\n### TUI & Themes\n\n#### Leader key\n\nOpenCode's TUI uses a **leader key** (default `ctrl+x`) followed by a single letter. Keeps single-keystroke editing keys free for the input box.\n\n`ctrl+x`\n\n| Binding | Action |\n| --- | --- |\n| `ctrl+x n` | New session |\n| `ctrl+x l` | List sessions |\n| `ctrl+x c` | Compact session |\n| `ctrl+x e` | Open external editor |\n| `ctrl+x m` | Browse models |\n| `ctrl+x t` | Switch theme |\n| `ctrl+x u` / `ctrl+x r` | Undo / Redo |\n| `ctrl+x q` | Quit |\n| `ctrl+p` | Command palette |\n| `Tab` | Cycle primary agents |\n| `Esc` | Cancel / dismiss |\n\n`ctrl+x n`\n`ctrl+x l`\n`ctrl+x c`\n`ctrl+x e`\n`ctrl+x m`\n`ctrl+x t`\n`ctrl+x u`\n`ctrl+x r`\n`ctrl+x q`\n`ctrl+p`\n`Tab`\n`Esc`\n\nReadline shortcuts also work inside the prompt box (`ctrl+a`, `ctrl+e`, `ctrl+k`, `ctrl+u`).\n\n`ctrl+a`\n`ctrl+e`\n`ctrl+k`\n`ctrl+u`\n\n#### Themes\n\nBuilt-in: `system` · `tokyonight` · `everforest` · `ayu` · `catppuccin` · `catppuccin-macchiato` · `gruvbox` · `kanagawa` · `nord` · `matrix` · `one-dark`. Set via `/themes` or `tui.json`.\n\n`system`\n`tokyonight`\n`everforest`\n`ayu`\n`catppuccin`\n`catppuccin-macchiato`\n`gruvbox`\n`kanagawa`\n`nord`\n`matrix`\n`one-dark`\n`/themes`\n`tui.json`\n\nCustom themes: `.opencode/themes/<name>.json` (project) or `~/.config/opencode/themes/<name>.json` (global). Truecolor terminals required.\n\n`.opencode/themes/<name>.json`\n`~/.config/opencode/themes/<name>.json`\n\n📚 Deep dive: [`docs/tui.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/tui.md) · [opencode.ai/docs/keybinds](https://opencode.ai/docs/keybinds) · [opencode.ai/docs/themes](https://opencode.ai/docs/themes).\n\n`docs/tui.md`\n\n### Headless & CI\n\nThree ways to run OpenCode unattended:\n\nUseful `run` flags: `--continue` / `--session <id>` (resume), `--fork` (branch a session), `--share` (publish), `--format json` (machine-readable), `--file <path>` (attach), `--replay` (interactive replay, v1.16+), `--dangerously-skip-permissions` (auto-approve everything not `deny` — **CI only**).\n\n`run`\n`--continue`\n`--session <id>`\n`--fork`\n`--share`\n`--format json`\n`--file <path>`\n`--replay`\n`--dangerously-skip-permissions`\n`deny`\n\nSessions, stats, sharing:\n\n📚 Full CLI reference: [`docs/reference/cli.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/reference/cli.md). CI recipes (GitHub Actions, GitLab CI): [`docs/workflows.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/workflows.md).\n\n`docs/reference/cli.md`\n`docs/workflows.md`\n\n### Sharing\n\n`/share` generates a public link to the current session (`opncd.ai/s/<id>`). Three modes via `opencode.json`:\n\n`/share`\n`opncd.ai/s/<id>`\n`opencode.json`\n\n`/unshare` revokes the link. Enterprise builds can enforce `\"disabled\"` via managed config.\n\n`/unshare`\n`\"disabled\"`\n\n⚠️ **Privacy:** Shared conversations live on OpenCode's servers until you unshare. Don't share sessions with secrets, proprietary code, or confidential data.\n\n## Extending OpenCode\n\nOpenCode has **five extension points**. Pick by trigger and surface:\n\n| Extension | Triggered by | Lives in |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| [Custom Commands](#custom-commands) | User typing `/<name>` | `.opencode/commands/*.md` |\n| [Agent Skills](#agent-skills) | Model auto-discovery (description match) | `.opencode/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` |\n| [Plugins](#plugins) | Lifecycle events (tool calls, file edits, sessions) | `.opencode/plugins/*.{js,ts}` |\n| [Agents](#agents) | Tab key or `@<name>` mention | `.opencode/agents/<name>.md` |\n| [MCP Servers](#mcp-servers) | Prompt-driven external tool use | `opencode.json` → `mcp` |\n\n`/<name>`\n`.opencode/commands/*.md`\n`.opencode/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`\n`.opencode/plugins/*.{js,ts}`\n`@<name>`\n`.opencode/agents/<name>.md`\n`opencode.json`\n`mcp`\n\n💡 These five compose. Most polished workflows combine 2–3.\n\n### Slash Commands\n\nOpenCode ships a set of built-in slash commands plus everything you write yourself.\n\n| Command | What it does |\n| --- | --- |\n| `/init` | Guided generation of `AGENTS.md` |\n| `/help` | Show the help dialog |\n| `/new` *(`/clear`)* | New session |\n| `/sessions` *(`/resume`, `/continue`)* | List and switch sessions |\n| `/models` | Browse models |\n| `/connect` | Add a provider |\n| `/themes` | Switch theme |\n| `/compact` *(`/summarize`)* | Compact session to save tokens |\n| `/share` · `/unshare` | Public link control |\n| `/export` | Export to markdown |\n| `/undo` · `/redo` | Walk edit history |\n| `/editor` | Open `$EDITOR` |\n| `/details` · `/thinking` | Toggle visibility of tool / reasoning blocks |\n| `/exit` *(`/quit`, `/q`)* | Exit |\n\n`/init`\n`AGENTS.md`\n`/help`\n`/new`\n`/clear`\n`/sessions`\n`/resume`\n`/continue`\n`/models`\n`/connect`\n`/themes`\n`/compact`\n`/summarize`\n`/share`\n`/unshare`\n`/export`\n`/undo`\n`/redo`\n`/editor`\n`$EDITOR`\n`/details`\n`/thinking`\n`/exit`\n`/quit`\n`/q`\n\nCustom commands can override built-ins with the same name.\n\n📚 Full reference: [`docs/reference/slash-commands.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/reference/slash-commands.md).\n\n`docs/reference/slash-commands.md`\n\n### Custom Commands\n\n**Mental model:** A custom command is a prompt template you've named. Save as `.opencode/commands/<name>.md`, invoke as `/<name>` in the TUI — with `$ARGUMENTS`, `@file`, and `!shell` interpolated at invocation time.\n\n`.opencode/commands/<name>.md`\n`/<name>`\n`$ARGUMENTS`\n`@file`\n`!shell`\n\nMinimal example:\n\nSave as `.opencode/commands/test.md` → invoke with `/test`.\n\n`.opencode/commands/test.md`\n`/test`\n\n| Frontmatter key | Purpose |\n| --- | --- |\n| `description` (required) | Shown in the slash-command palette |\n| `agent` | Which agent runs it (`build`, `plan`, or custom) |\n| `model` | Override the model just for this command |\n| `subtask` | `true` runs as a subagent (isolated child session) |\n\n`description`\n`agent`\n`build`\n`plan`\n`model`\n`subtask`\n`true`\n\n| Body placeholder | Substitutes |\n| --- | --- |\n| `$ARGUMENTS` / `$1` / `$2` | Text after the command name |\n| `@<path>` | File content (fuzzy resolved) |\n| ``!<cmd>`` | Shell stdout |\n\n`$ARGUMENTS`\n`$1`\n`$2`\n`@<path>`\n``!<cmd>``\n\nThis repo ships four examples in [`.opencode/commands/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/commands): `/review`, `/pr`, `/test`, `/optimize`.\n\n`.opencode/commands/`\n`/review`\n`/pr`\n`/test`\n`/optimize`\n\n📚 Deep dive: [`docs/commands.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/commands.md) · [opencode.ai/docs/commands](https://opencode.ai/docs/commands).\n\n`docs/commands.md`\n\n### Agent Skills\n\n**Mental model:** A skill is a **discoverable** workflow. The agent sees the skill's `name` and `description` and decides on its own to load it when the task matches. You don't have to remember to invoke — the model does.\n\n`name`\n`description`\n\nOpenCode uses Claude Code-compatible Agent Skill folders. Lookup paths (project → global → Claude-compat → Agent-compat):\n\n`.opencode/skills/<name>/SKILL.md\n~/.config/opencode/skills/<name>/SKILL.md\n.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md\n.agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`\n\nEach `SKILL.md` needs YAML frontmatter with a `name` (lowercase-kebab, ≤64 chars) and a `description` (1–1024 chars). **The description is the discovery signal** — write it like a trigger sentence the agent will recognize.\n\n`SKILL.md`\n`name`\n`description`\n\n**Command vs. skill, in one line:** commands are user-invoked (`/<name>`), skills are model-invoked (description match). Write both for the same workflow if you want both surfaces.\n\n`/<name>`\n\nThis repo ships one example: [`.opencode/skills/git-release/SKILL.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/skills/git-release/SKILL.md).\n\n`.opencode/skills/git-release/SKILL.md`\n\n📚 Deep dive: [`docs/skills.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/skills.md) · [opencode.ai/docs/skills](https://opencode.ai/docs/skills).\n\n`docs/skills.md`\n\n### Plugins\n\n**Mental model:** Plugins are OpenCode's **event-driven extension surface** — small JavaScript or TypeScript modules that subscribe to lifecycle events (tool calls, file edits, session state) and run code automatically. `husky` for your AI session.\n\n`husky`\n\nTwo locations:\n\n`.opencode/plugins/<name>.{js,ts} # project\n~/.config/opencode/plugins/<name>.{js,ts} # global`\n\nPlus npm packages via the `plugin` array in `opencode.json`:\n\n`plugin`\n`opencode.json`\n\nAuto-installed via Bun, cached under `~/.cache/opencode/node_modules/`.\n\n`~/.cache/opencode/node_modules/`\n\nPlugins receive `{ project, directory, worktree, client, $ }` and return hooks. `$` is the Bun shell. Two shapes: typed hooks like `tool.execute.before`/`shell.env` that get `(input, output)`, and a generic `event` handler for the lifecycle stream (files, sessions, messages, permissions, LSP, TUI — ~26 events).\n\n`{ project, directory, worktree, client, $ }`\n`$`\n`tool.execute.before`\n`shell.env`\n`(input, output)`\n`event`\n\nThis repo ships two working examples in [`.opencode/plugins/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/plugins):\n\n`.opencode/plugins/`\n\n| File | What it does |\n| --- | --- |\n| [`protect-secrets.js`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/plugins/protect-secrets.js) | Blocks any tool call touching `.env*`, `secrets/`, SSH keys |\n| [`audit-log.js`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/.opencode/plugins/audit-log.js) | Appends every successful tool call to `.opencode/audit.jsonl` |\n\n`protect-secrets.js`\n`.env*`\n`secrets/`\n`audit-log.js`\n`.opencode/audit.jsonl`\n\n⚠️ **Security:** Plugins run arbitrary code with your user permissions. Read every third-party plugin before installing — exactly like reviewing a shell script before sourcing.\n\n📚 Deep dive: [`docs/plugins.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/plugins.md) · [opencode.ai/docs/plugins](https://opencode.ai/docs/plugins).\n\n`docs/plugins.md`\n\n### Agents\n\nOpenCode ships five built-in agents, and you can define your own as markdown files.\n\n#### Built-in\n\n| Agent | Mode | Tools | Reach for it when… |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `build` | primary (default) | All | Default daily-driver — implementation, refactors |\n| `plan` | primary | `edit` and `bash` default to `ask` | Read-only-ish analysis, exploration |\n| `general` | subagent | All minus `todowrite` | Multi-step tasks isolated from main session |\n| `explore` | subagent | `read`, `grep`, `glob`, `list` | \"Where is X?\" code search |\n| `scout` | subagent | `webfetch`, `websearch`, + read tools | External docs and dependency research |\n\n`build`\n`plan`\n`edit`\n`bash`\n`ask`\n`general`\n`todowrite`\n`explore`\n`read`\n`grep`\n`glob`\n`list`\n`scout`\n`webfetch`\n`websearch`\n\n`Tab` cycles primaries. `@<name>` invokes a subagent.\n\n`Tab`\n`@<name>`\n\n#### Custom\n\nDrop a markdown file in `.opencode/agents/`:\n\n`.opencode/agents/`\n\nFilename → agent name. `frontend-engineer.md` → `@frontend-engineer` (subagent) or in the Tab cycle (primary). The `mode` value picks the surface:\n\n`frontend-engineer.md`\n`@frontend-engineer`\n`mode`\n\n| `mode` | Where it appears |\n| --- | --- |\n| `primary` | Tab cycle alongside `build` / `plan` |\n| `subagent` | `@<name>` mentions only (runs in a child session) |\n| `all` | Both |\n\n`mode`\n`primary`\n`build`\n`plan`\n`subagent`\n`@<name>`\n`all`\n\nBash permissions accept a **glob-pattern map** (`{\"*\": \"ask\", \"git status*\": \"allow\", \"rm -rf*\": \"deny\"}`) — rules match in order and the **last matching rule wins**, so list the catch-all `*` first.\n\n`{\"*\": \"ask\", \"git status*\": \"allow\", \"rm -rf*\": \"deny\"}`\n`*`\n\n📐 This repo ships **drop-in specialist prompts** in [`specialized-agents/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/specialized-agents) — backend, frontend, code reviewer, security reviewer, tech lead, database, UX. Copy any of them into `.opencode/agents/<name>.md` to use.\n\n`specialized-agents/`\n`.opencode/agents/<name>.md`\n\n📚 Deep dive — full frontmatter key list, all 15 permission keys, JSON-form alternative: [`docs/agents.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/agents.md) · [`docs/reference/permissions.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/reference/permissions.md).\n\n`docs/agents.md`\n`docs/reference/permissions.md`\n\n### MCP Servers\n\nMCP is the universal connector that lets OpenCode talk to **external tools** — browsers, databases, search engines, ticketing systems — through one open protocol. USB-C for AI integrations.\n\nDeclare servers in the `mcp` section of `opencode.json`. Local servers spawn a subprocess; remote servers hit an HTTPS endpoint with automatic OAuth via Dynamic Client Registration (RFC 7591).\n\n`mcp`\n`opencode.json`\n\nManage from the CLI: `opencode mcp add | list | auth <name> | logout <name> | debug <name>`. Reference a server's tools in a prompt with `use <server-name>`.\n\n`opencode mcp add | list | auth <name> | logout <name> | debug <name>`\n`use <server-name>`\n\nFeatured walkthroughs in [`mcp-servers/`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/mcp-servers):\n\n`mcp-servers/`\n\n| Server | What it adds |\n| --- | --- |\n| [Playwright](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/mcp-servers/playwright.md) | Browser automation — DOM, network, screenshots, accessibility |\n| [Context7](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/mcp-servers/context7.md) | Live, version-pinned library docs piped into the prompt |\n| [Sentry](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/mcp-servers/sentry.md) | Errors, traces, releases |\n| [Grep by Vercel](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/mcp-servers/grep.md) | Code search across GitHub |\n\n⚠️ **Token budget:** MCP tools land in the model's tool surface every turn — heavy servers can easily eat 10K+ tokens of context. Disable noisy tools with the `tools` map (e.g. `\"github_*\": false`).\n\n`tools`\n`\"github_*\": false`\n\n📚 Deep dive: [`docs/mcp.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/mcp.md) · [opencode.ai/docs/mcp-servers](https://opencode.ai/docs/mcp-servers) · [Registry](https://registry.modelcontextprotocol.io/).\n\n`docs/mcp.md`\n\n## Reference\n\n### FAQ\n\n*[→ Full FAQ in `docs/reference/faq.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/reference/faq.md)*\n\n`docs/reference/faq.md`\n\n**Is OpenCode free?**\nThe software is open source (MIT). You pay for whichever LLM provider you use. [OpenCode Zen](#opencode-zen) is pay-as-you-go starting at fractions of a cent per request; BYOK works for direct providers.\n\n**Does OpenCode work without an internet connection?**\nYes, with a local model (Ollama, LM Studio, llama.cpp). Network is needed for hosted providers, remote MCP servers, sharing, and updates.\n\n**Can I migrate from Claude Code?**\nMost concepts map cleanly but a few fields and file paths differ. OpenCode reads `CLAUDE.md` and `.claude/skills/` as fallbacks. Slash commands move from `.claude/commands/` → `.opencode/commands/`; Python hooks become JS/TS plugins; agent frontmatter uses different keys (`name` gone, `mode` new, `tools` becomes `permission`). See [the full migration guide](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/migration.md).\n\n`CLAUDE.md`\n`.claude/skills/`\n`.claude/commands/`\n`.opencode/commands/`\n`name`\n`mode`\n`tools`\n`permission`\n\n**Custom commands vs. skills — which should I write?**\nBoth. Commands are **explicit** (user types `/<name>`); skills are **discoverable** (model picks them up). Use commands for workflows the user owns, skills for expertise the agent should reach for. Comparison in [`docs/commands.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/commands.md#when-to-use-a-command-vs-a-skill-vs-an-agent).\n\n`/<name>`\n`docs/commands.md`\n\n**How do I keep OpenCode from running risky shell commands?**\nSet `bash` permission to `\"ask\"` at the project level, or use the glob form to whitelist only safe patterns. Full mechanism in [`docs/reference/permissions.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/reference/permissions.md).\n\n`bash`\n`\"ask\"`\n`docs/reference/permissions.md`\n\n**Where do I see my token usage?**\n`opencode stats` for a multi-day breakdown by model and project. The TUI also surfaces per-session totals in the footer.\n\n`opencode stats`\n\n### Updates & Deprecations\n\n*[→ Full changelog in `docs/reference/changelog.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/reference/changelog.md)*\n\n`docs/reference/changelog.md`\n\n**Current release:** **v1.16.2** *(2026-06-05)*. Run `opencode upgrade` to get it.\n\n`opencode upgrade`\n\n**New in v1.16:**\n\n`SKILL.md`\n`opencode agent create`\n`opencode run --replay`\n\n**Still recent (v1.15):**\n\n`opencode acp`\n`/Library/Application Support/opencode/`\n`/etc/opencode/`\n`%ProgramData%\\opencode`\n`CLAUDE.md`\n\n💡 Source of truth: [GitHub releases](https://github.com/anomalyco/opencode/releases).\n\n### References\n\n*[→ Full reading list in `docs/reference/further-reading.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/docs/reference/further-reading.md)*\n\n`docs/reference/further-reading.md`\n\n**Most-clicked starting points:**\n\n**Reading tips:** Anchor links work natively on GitHub — tap the table-of-contents button at the top of the file view. On a phone, stick to [Choose your path](#-choose-your-path); wider tables read best on desktop.\n\nFeatures, pricing, and availability change frequently. Always check the [official OpenCode documentation](https://opencode.ai/docs/) for the most current information.\n\n*Last reviewed 2026-06-08 · OpenCode v1.16.2 · Spotted something stale? [Open an issue](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/issues) or send a PR — see [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md).*\n\n`CONTRIBUTING.md`\n\n## About\n\nThe ultimate all-in-one guide to mastering OpenCode. From installation, Zen model router setup, TUI mastery, commands, skills, agents, workflows, automation, and integrations, to MCP servers, plugins, packed with step-by-step tutorials, real-world examples, and expert strategies to make this the global go-to repo for OpenCode mastery.\n\n### Resources\n\n### License\n\n### Code of conduct\n\n### Contributing\n\n### Security policy\n\n### Uh oh!\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\n### Stars\n\n### Watchers\n\n### Forks\n\n## [Releases](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/releases)\n\n## [Packages 0](/users/wesammustafa/packages?repo_name=OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know)\n\n### Uh oh!\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\n## [Contributors](/wesammustafa/OpenCode-Everything-You-Need-to-Know/graphs/contributors)\n\n### Uh oh!\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\nThere was an error while loading. Please reload this page.\n\n## Languages\n\n## Footer\n\n### Footer navigation"}, {"url": "https://github.com/opencode-ai/opencode", "title": "GitHub - opencode-ai/opencode: A powerful AI coding agent. Built ...", "content": "| .gitignore | .gitignore | feat: add github copilot provider (  feat: add github copilot  fix: add support for claude4\")#230)  feat: add github copilot  fix: add support for claude4\") | Jun 25, 2025 |\n| .goreleaser.yml | .goreleaser.yml | update aur | May 14, 2025 |\n| .opencode.json | .opencode.json | config validation | Apr 21, 2025 |\n| LICENSE | LICENSE | add license | Apr 21, 2025 |\n| README.md | README.md | docs(readme): update archive note: update archive note\") | Sep 18, 2025 |\n| go.mod | go.mod | refactor: upgrade Anthropic SDK to v1.4.0 an